    "content": "A shocking report from Education Cannot Wait exposes an educational catastrophe unfolding in Somalia, where millions of children are being left behind. Persistent instability, weak institutions, and repeated climate shocks have created a perfect storm, leaving the country with one of the lowest primary school attendance rates in the world.\n\nAccording to the report, under a third of school-age boys are enrolled in primary school, and the situation for girls is even worse. Access to secondary education is nearly nonexistent, with only a tiny fraction of children attending. Children uprooted by conflict or natural disasters are hit hardest: nearly two-thirds of displaced children have had their education interrupted and may never return to the classroom.\n\nClimate-induced crises, including cyclones, flooding, and drought, are wreaking havoc on communities across Puntland State and beyond. These disasters regularly displace families and destroy critical infrastructure like schools. Adding to the misery, ongoing conflict and violence continue to force families to flee, leaving children without access to safe learning environments.\n\nSince 2017, Education Cannot Wait has been working with partners to address this crisis, focusing on increasing enrolment and retention, especially for girls. Their programs include building and repairing schools, training teachers, running awareness campaigns about the importance of education, and providing nutritious school meals. However, the scale of the need remains overwhelming, and millions of children are still being denied their right to learn.",
